== In popular culture ==
*The 2002 M. Night Shyamalan directed science fiction horror film &quot;Signs&quot; was primarily filmed in Doylestown.
*The 2002 ESPN documentary &quot;The Last Game&quot;, tells the story of Central Bucks High School West&#x27;s football team and its long-standing coach Mike Pettine as the team seeks to defend its 30-game winning streak against major eastern Pennsylvania high school football powerhouses in Pettine&#x27;s final season before retirement.
*The HBO series &quot;The Gilded Age&quot;, which premiered in 2022, revolves around two separate Doylestown families who relocate to New York City in the late 1800s. However, the scenes set in Doylestown were filmed in Newport, Rhode Island.
*The 2024 epic historical drama film &quot;The Brutalist&quot; is partially set in the borough.

